\par\ql\{bml SC_Status.bmp\}\par\ql

<color=6b>INFORMATION</color>
	<color=5b>Mode:</color> What Background Pi is currently doing.
	<color=5b>% Complete:</color> What % of the current task has been completed.
	<color=5b>Time Elapsed:</color> How long Backpi has been running on the current calculation.
	<color=5b>Time Remaining:</color> How much time remains in the current task.
	<color=5b>Total Time:</color> The total amount of time the task will take.
	<color=5b>Iteration Time:</color> How long each iteration takes.
	<color=5b>Iteration:</color> What "iteration" of the current calculation it is on.
	<color=5b>Est. # Iterations:</color> The way the algorythm is designed, the # of iterations can only be predicted in a reasonable amount of time.
	<color=5b>Calculation:</color> For calculation mode, tells the first digit position in the nine being calculated.
----- SHM ---- page 5 ---- 
\par\ql\{bml SC_Config.bmp\}\par\ql

<color=6b>INFORMATION</color>
 	<color=5b>Host:</color> The domain address of the the server to connect to. You shouldn't change this. Ex:
		<color=10><b>Correct:</b> www.example.com</color>
		<color=4><b>Incorrect:</b> http://www.example.com</color>
	<color=5b>Port:</color> The network port on the host to connect to. You shouldn't change this.
	<color=5b>Timeout:</color> Upon failure, BackPi will wait this long before trying again.

	<color=5b>Resume:</color> The amount of time in seconds between resume data saves. Set to 0 (zero) to NOT save resume data.
	<color=5b>Delay:</color> If > 0, BackPi will wait this long in milliseconds after each iteration.  This reduces CPU usage on your system.  A value of 10 or lower should be fine.

\par\ql\{bml SC_Config_Save.bmp\}\par\ql

<color=6b>INFORMATION</color>
	<color=5b>Yes:</color> Save and close the configuration editor.
	<color=5b>No:</color> Close the configuration editor without saving.
	<color=5b>Cancel:</color> Go back to the configuration editor.
