Error on Comm
<color=6b>Q:</color>
Background Pi shows a icon with a yellow <b>!</b> on two arrows.
<color=6b>A:</color>
This may mean a few things:
<color=5>1)</color> The Server Is Down
<color=5>2)</color> The server is incorrectly entered into the configuration file
<color=5>3)</color> Your ISP, Firewall, or Router is blocking port 31415
Allow a day or two, if its still not communicating, try looking for updates or checking settings.


System Requirements
<color=6b>Q:</color>
What are the minimum system requirements for Background Pi?
<color=6b>A:</color>
<color=5b>OS:</color> Tested on: XP, Linux with Wine
<color=5b>Storage:</color> Aprox. 3 megabytes of hard drive space

<color=5b>Additional Considerations:</color>
<color=4>1) </color>An internet connection, preferably connected at least once per day.
<color=4>3) </color>Background pi saves every 20 seconds; please do NOT enable hard drive off as an energy feature. <jump=SHM_contents0008>More Info...</jump>

----- SHM ---- page 7 ---- 
\par\ql\{bml SC_Powermanagement.bmp\}\par\ql

<color=6b>INFORMATION</color>
These are the suggested settings for energy star compliant systems. You can access the Power Management dialog through the screen saver tab in Display Properties, along with through Control Panel.  Please do <b>NOT</b> activate "Hard Disk Off" or "System Standby" for they do not allow Background Pi to keep running.  You may have "Monitor Off" enabled; we suggest that you enable "Monitor Off"  with no screensaver if your monitor is energy star compliant.  However, if it is not, please DISABLE this and use blank screen as your screen saver (below).

\par\ql\{bml SC_Displayproperties.bmp\}\par\ql

<color=6b>INFORMATION</color>
This shows blank screen as the screen saver, this is also where you get into the Power Management dialog, along with through Control Panel.
